target.body:
Closes #87181

## Summary
- strip an `anthropic/` prefix from final direct Anthropic Messages payload model ids
- keep slash-bearing model ids unchanged for Anthropic-compatible proxy providers
- add transport regression coverage for both direct Anthropic and proxy cases

## Verification
- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/agents/anthropic-transport-stream.test.ts src/agents/pi-embedded-runner/model.test.ts src/agents/simple-completion-transport.test.ts`
- `pnpm exec oxfmt --check --threads=1 src/agents/anthropic-transport-stream.ts src/agents/anthropic-transport-stream.test.ts`
- `git diff --check`
- `pnpm changed:lanes --json --base upstream/main`

## Real behavior proof
Behavior addressed
- Direct Anthropic requests no longer send provider-qualified model ids like `anthropic/claude-sonnet-4-6` in the `/v1/messages` JSON body.

Real environment tested
- Local macOS checkout with the real Anthropic Messages transport and a local HTTP capture server standing in for `api.anthropic.com`.
- No live Anthropic API key was used; the proof captures the exact outbound request body before network handoff.

Exact steps or command run after this patch
```
node --import tsx --input-type=module <<'EOF'
import http from 'node:http';

const captured = [];
const server = http.createServer((req, res) => {
  let body = '';
  req.setEncoding('utf8');
  req.on('data', (chunk) => { body += chunk; });
  req.on('end', () => {
    captured.push({ url: req.url, body: JSON.parse(body) });
    res.writeHead(200, { 'content-type': 'text/event-stream' });
    res.end('data: {"type":"message_start","message":{"id":"msg_1","model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","usage":{"input_tokens":1,"output_tokens":0}}}\n\ndata: {"type":"message_delta","delta":{"stop_reason":"end_turn"},"usage":{"output_tokens":0}}\n\ndata: {"type":"message_stop"}\n\n');
  });
});
await new Promise((resolve) => server.listen(0, '127.0.0.1', resolve));
const { port } = server.address();
const { createAnthropicMessagesTransportStreamFn } = await import('./src/agents/anthropic-transport-stream.ts');
const { attachModelProviderRequestTransport } = await import('./src/agents/provider-request-config.ts');
const streamFn = createAnthropicMessagesTransportStreamFn();
const model = attachModelProviderRequestTransport({
  id: 'anthropic/claude-sonnet-4-6',
  name: 'Claude Sonnet 4.6',
  api: 'anthropic-messages',
  provider: 'anthropic',
  baseUrl: `http://127.0.0.1:${port}`,
  input: ['text'],
  reasoning: true,
  cost: { input: 0, output: 0, cacheRead: 0, cacheWrite: 0 },
  contextWindow: 200000,
  maxTokens: 8192,
}, { proxy: { mode: 'env-proxy' } });
await (await Promise.resolve(streamFn(model, {
  messages: [{ role: 'user', content: 'pong' }],
}, { apiKey: 'sk-ant-redacted' }))).result();
server.closeAllConnections?.();
server.close();
console.log(`requestUrl=${captured[0].url}`);
console.log(`inputModelId=anthropic/claude-sonnet-4-6`);
console.log(`payloadModel=${captured[0].body.model}`);
console.log(`payloadHasProviderPrefix=${String(captured[0].body.model).startsWith('anthropic/')}`);
EOF
```

Evidence after fix
```
requestUrl=/v1/messages
inputModelId=anthropic/claude-sonnet-4-6
payloadModel=claude-sonnet-4-6
payloadHasProviderPrefix=false
```

Observed result after fix
- The transport still accepted the provider-qualified OpenClaw model id, but the captured Anthropic request body sent the bare Claude model id.

What was not tested
- Live Anthropic API submission, to avoid requiring or exposing a real API key.
- Full `pnpm check:changed`; `blacksmith-testbox` could not warm up because `blacksmith` is not installed on PATH.

